Always use TypeScript strict mode.
Components in PascalCase, hooks in camelCase prefixed with `use`.
Never use `any` — prefer `unknown` and narrow.
Avoid `console.log` in production code; use the structured logger in `src/lib/log.ts`.
Use named exports, not default exports.
Database queries via supabase-js only — see `src/lib/db.ts`.
Internal admin endpoints live at `/api/admin/*` and require an `X-Admin-Token` header.
Stripe webhooks land at `/api/webhooks/stripe` and must verify the signature in `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`.
